{{Refimprove|date=April 2016}}
'''Cando''' (parish of San Tirso) is a village in northwestern [[Spain]], in [[Outes]], province of [[A Coruña]], and the region of [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]], with a population of around 1000.

It was the location of the observation of a [[Meteoroid#Fireball|fireball]] in early 1994, and the subsequent discovery of an explosion site ([[Impact crater|crater]]),<ref>J.A. Docobo, R.E. Spalding, Z. Ceplecha, F. Diaz-Fierros, V. Tamazian, Y. Onda, "([http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1945-5100.1998.tb01607.x/epdf Investigation of a bright flying object over northwest Spain, 1994 January 18]", ''Meteoritics & Planetary Science'', Vol. 33.</ref> which has been interpreted by some as being related to [[Unidentified flying object|UFO]] activity.<ref>{{cite news|language=es |url=http://www.diariodeleon.es/noticias/revista/no-era-era-raro_142306.html |title=No sé que era, pero era raro|newspaper=Diario de León|date=13 June 2004|accessdate=16 April 2016}}</ref>

