{{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | name = René Fernández Apaza | title = Archbishop of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Cochabamba|Archdiocese of Cochabamba]] (emeritus) | image = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Roman Catholic Church]] | archdiocese = | diocese = | see = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Cochabamba]] | term = 1988 - 1999 | predecessor = Gennaro Maria Prata Vuolo, S.D.B | successor = Tito Solari Capellari, S.D.B. <!-- Orders --> | ordination = November 28, 1948 | ordinated_by = | consecration = | consecrated_by = | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = {{Birth date|1924|1|9}} | birth_place = [[Padilla, Bolivia]] | death_date = {{dda|2013|8|14|1924|1|9}} | death_place = [[Cochabamba, Bolivia]] | previous_post = Prelate }}
'''René Fernández Apaza''' (January 9, 1924 – August 14, 2013) was a [[Bolivia]]n [[Prelate]] of [[Roman Catholic Church]].<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bfarnap.html Rene Ferdandez Apaza]</ref>
René Fernández Apaza was born in [[Padilla, Bolivia]] ordained a priest on November 28, 1948. Fernández was appointed bishop to the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Oruro|Diocese of Oruro]] on March 2, 1968, and consecrated on April 21, 1968. Fernández was appointed to the [[Military Bishopric of Bolivia]] on July 30, 1975, and would resign on May 17, 1986. Fernández was appointed [[Coadjutor Archbishop]] of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Sucre|Archdiocese of Sucre]] November 21, 1981 and succeeds on November 30, 1983. Fernández' s final appointment came on April 16, 1988, to the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Cochabamba|Archdiocese of Cochabamba]] where he would remain until retiring July 8, 1999.
He died of an apparent heart attack on August 14, 2013.<ref>http://www.radiofides.com/noticia/Sociedad/Murio_Monsenor_Rene_Fernandez_Apaza</ref>
