'''[[Maharaja]] Sher Singh''' (4 December 1807 – 15 September 1843) was a son of Maharaja [[Ranjit Singh]]. In 1841, he became [[Maharaja]] of the [[Sikh Empire]] and the [[Punjab region|Punjab]]. 

In 1820, Maharaja Ranjit Singh granted him the privilege of being seated in the Darbar and bestowed civil and military honours on him. From 1831 to 1834 he acted as Governor of Kashmir and in 1834 he was a commander in the force that captured [[Peshawar]] from the Afghans.<ref name=Hasrat/>

==Birth==
He was the son of Maharaja [[Ranjit Singh]] and Maharani [[Mehtab Kaur]], who was also the mother of Prince Tara Singh (1807-1859). (Mehtab Kaur, who was also known as Mahitab Kaur, is not to be confused with Maharani Mahtab Devi Sahiba, daughter of Maharaja Sansar Chand of Kangra, another wife, who committed ''sati'' in 1839 with Ranjit Singh lying with his head on her lap.)

==Reign==
[[File:The Maha-raja Shere Singh.jpg|thumb|left|150px|The Maharaja Sher Singh]]
He became Maharaja on 27 January 1841,<ref name=Hasrat>{{cite web |url=http://www.learnpunjabi.org/eos/index.aspx |title=Sher Singh, Maharaja |last1=Hasrat |first1=B.J. |work=Encyclopaedia of Sikhism, Editor-in-Chief Harbans Singh |publisher=Punjab University Patiala}}</ref>  after the sudden death of [[Nau Nihal Singh]] whose death was set in motion, some say purposely, while returning from his father's cremation. He was the half brother of [[Nau Nihal Singh]]'s father, Maharaja [[Kharak Singh]].

Proclaimed Maharaja by his [[vizier|wazir]] (prime minister) [[Dhian Singh]] Dogra, he won the throne after a protracted siege of the [[Lahore Fort]] which was held by the Royal family. Thousands died in the siege. 

[[File:Maharaja Sher Singh (1807-1843) seated, attended by his council in the Lahore Fort..jpg|thumb|300px|Maharaja Sher Singh (1807-1843) seated, attended by his council in the Lahore Fort.]]

Historians record that he was not very smart politically and let the Dogra brothers take charge of all functions of state. The Dogras, like puppet masters, pulled the strings of others to bring about the death of Sher Singh. 

Sher Singh was killed as he reached for a new shotgun held by Ajit Singh Sandhawalia, who pulled the trigger. Sher Singh only had time to utter, "what treachery."  The Sandhawalias also murdered Dhian Singh. The Sandhawalias were thought to have also had designs on the empire.

==Legacy==
His palace is leased to [[Baring Union Christian College]].

