{{Infobox mountain | name = Spirit Mountain | photo = Spirit Mountain from west 1.jpg | photo_caption = View from the west | elevation_ft = 5642 | elevation_ref = {{NAVD88}}<ref name="ngs">{{cite ngs |id=FS1078 |name=Spirit |accessdate=2008-11-23}}</ref> | prominence_ft = 2879 | prominence_ref = <ref name="pb">{{cite peakbagger |pid=3796 |name=Spirit Mountain, Nevada |accessdate=2008-04-05}}</ref> | location = [[Clark County, Nevada]], U.S. | range = Eldorado-Newberry Mountains | coordinates = {{coord|35.274977972|N|114.723384419|W|type:mountain_region:US-NV_scale:100000_source:NGS|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | coordinates_ref = <ref name="ngs"/> | topo = [[United States Geological Survey|USGS]] Spirit Mountain | first_ascent = | easiest_route = | embedded = {{Infobox NRHP | embed=yes | name = Spirit Mountain | nrhp_type = | image = | caption = | location = | nearest_city = [[Laughlin, Nevada]] | area = | added = September 8, 1999 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | refnum = 99001083 | mpsub = | governing_body = National Park Service }} }} '''Spirit Mountain''', also known as '''Avi Kwa' Ame''' in [[Mojave language|Mojave]], is a mountain in the [[Laughlin, Nevada|Laughlin]], [[Nevada]] area that is listed on the United States [[National Register of Historic Places]]. It is part of the [[Newberry Mountains (Nevada)|Newberry Mountains]] in Nevada and the summit is the highest point in the [[Spirit Mountain Wilderness]].<ref name="pb"/><ref> {{cite web | url = http://www.wilderness.net/index.cfm?fuse=NWPS&sec=wildView&WID=573 | title = Spirit Mountain Wilderness | publisher = Wilderness.net | accessdate = 2008-12-30 }}</ref>
== History == Spirit Mountain is the center of creation for all Yuman speakers.<ref> {{cite journal | last = Boholm | first = Åsa | last2 = Löfstdedt | first2 = Ragnar E. | journal = Risk, Society and Policy Series | title = Faculty Siting: Risk, Power and Identity in Land Use Planning | url = http://web.arizona.edu/~swst/faculty/facility_siting.pdf | accessdate = 2008-04-05 }}</ref>
The mountain, listed as a [[Traditional Cultural Property]], was listed on the National Register of Historic Places on September 8, 1999.<ref> {{cite web |url = http://nvshpo.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=86&Itemid=9 |title = Nevada Entries in the National Register of Historic Places: Clark County |publisher = Nevada State Historic Preservation Office |accessdate = 2008-04-05 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110725164454/http://nvshpo.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=86&Itemid=9 |archivedate = 2011-07-25 |df = }}</ref><ref> {{cite web | url = http://www.nps.gov/history/NR/listings/990917.htm | title = Weekly list of actions taken on properties 9/06/99 through 9/10/99 | publisher = National Park Service | accessdate = 2008-04-05 }}</ref>
