In [[Chinese Buddhism]], '''Zhu Zixing''' is described as the first [[Chinese people|Chinese]] to be [[ordination|ordained]] and become a Buddhist via contact with others on the [[Silk Road]]. Zhu first went to [[central Asia]] in 260 to investigate [[Buddhism]], long before other Chinese [[monk]]s and travelers reached [[India]] to study Buddhism.
